step1 - gsutil mb -l us-central1 gs://your-bucket-name

step2 -
mkdir gcs-function
cd gcs-function

step3 - Create a Python file (main.py) and write the function:

import functions_framework
@functions_framework.cloud_event
def gcs_trigger(cloud_event):
"""Triggered by a change in a Cloud Storage
bucket."""
data = cloud_event.data

file_name = data["name"]
bucket_name = data["bucket"]
size = data.get("size", "Unknown size")

print(f"File {file_name} uploaded to
{bucket_name}, size: {size} bytes")


Step 4: Create the requirements.txt File

echo "functions-framework==3.*" >
requirements.txt

OR
vi requirements.txt
And write the dependency info as:
functions-framework==3.*

Step 5: Deploy the Cloud Function
Run the following command to deploy the function:
gcloud functions deploy gcs_trigger \
--gen2 \
--runtime=python311 \
--region=us-central1 \
--source=. \
--entry-point=gcs_trigger \

--trigger-event-filters="type=google.cloud.st
orage.object.v1.finalized" \

--trigger-event-filters="bucket=your-bucket-name
" \ --allow-unauthenticated

Step 6: Test the Function

Upload a file to the bucket:
echo "Hello Cloud Function!" > test.txt
OR
vi test.txt
And write the content: Hello Cloud
Function!

Then, execute the following command:
gsutil cp test.txt gs://your-bucket-name/

Check logs:
gcloud functions logs read gcs_trigger
--region=us-central1
